      "content": "You'll likely want to skip that grapefruit blast with your atorvastatin! Grapefruit juice inhibits the enzyme that breaks down your statin, meaning it can cause toxic levels of the drug in your system. To keep your cholesterol in check without drama, switch to an orange or supplement with a small dose of pure Vitamin C. Stick to the juice plan, but do it on an empty stomach, and never mix it with these meds!",
